entry.title: Row: 2
entry.content: speakertitle: Ankur Kotwal, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Ankur is a Developer Advocate for Android at Google. He works closely with app developers, helping them bring rich, compelling and high quality apps to the Android Market. Ankur is an experienced software engineer in scalable, high-performance, mission critical enterprise software with a passion for mobile technologies., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/ankur_kotwal.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/113640716072608481822/about

entry.title: Row: 3
entry.content: speakertitle: Iein Valdez, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Iein is a Developer Advocate who spends most of his time focused on Google App Engine. He is passionate about accelerating Google cloud adoption within startup communities, enterprise ecosystems and strategic partners. Previously he spent his career working for several startups in the cloud computing, healthcare, financial services, and hr space., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/iein_valdez.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/103073491679741548297/about

entry.title: Row: 4
entry.content: speakertitle: Timothy Jordan, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Timothy is a Developer Advocate working on the social web. He has taught broadcasting, theater, programming, and various forms of new media at UC Santa Cruz, the Academy of Art University, and the Digital Media Academy. He has a B.S. in Computer Engineering, a Theater Arts graduate degree, and an MFA in Digital Arts and New Media from UC Santa Cruz. In his spare time he runs half marathons and announces for the Santa Cruz Derby Girls, the Silicon Valley Roller Girls, and any other Roller Derby team that asks. As an engineer he enjoys solving problems for the benefit of fellow humans. As an artist he enjoys the search for truth and beauty., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/timothy_jordan.jpg, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/113751353481962008916/about

entry.title: Row: 5
entry.content: speakertitle: Peng Ying, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Peng is a Developer Programs Engineer for Google Commerce. He's helped developers integrate Google Checkout for over 3 years. His main language is currently Java (App Engine) but he works with PHP, Python and ASP Classic as well. Peng graduated from Johns Hopkins in 2005., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/peng_ying.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/115132759088093329854/about

entry.title: Row: 6
entry.content: speakertitle: Tony Chan, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Tony joined Google in 2007 as a Developer Programs Engineer. Since then, he has helped developers with various Google products/APIs like Google Checkout, Apps and Android. Currently, Tony is a developer advocate for Android. Prior to joining Google, Tony was a senior applications developer at the University of Michigan and a management consultant at PricewaterhouseCooper., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/tony_chan.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/100444819261782786795/about

entry.title: Row: 7
entry.content: speakertitle: Eric Bidelman, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Eric is a Developer Programs Engineer on Google's Chrome Developer Relations team. Over the last two years he's worked on various developer focused products, including Google Docs, Sites, Health, and OAuth. Recently, Eric joined the Chrome team to help spread HTML5 goodness around the globe. He is the author of the book "Using the HTML5 Filesystem API". Prior to Google, Eric worked as a software engineer at the University of Michigan where he designed rich web applications and APIs for the university's 19 libraries., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/eric_bidelman.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/118075919496626375791/about

entry.title: Row: 8
entry.content: speakertitle: Andrew Gerrand, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Andrew is Developer Advocate and member of the Go Programming Language team at Google. He writes Go articles and tutorials, gives Go talks and workshops, does Go code reviews, and writes Go code. He also manages the Go community, web site (golang.org), and continuous build infrastructure (for the Go project). (Can you see a pattern here?) Before joining Google, Andrew was a consultant programmer at companies ranging from web startups to Internet Providers. He has also worked as a composer, photographer, SCUBA diver, and concert tour manager (although not at the same time)., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/andrew_gerrand.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/106356964679457436995/about

entry.title: Row: 9
entry.content: speakertitle: Steve Bazyl, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Steve is a Developer Advocate at Google focused on developers integrating with Google Apps. Prior to Google he worked at IGT and RSA Security as a software architected building highly scalable and secure web based systems., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/steve_bazyl.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/103354693083460731603/about

entry.title: Row: 10
entry.content: speakertitle: Eiji Kitamura, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Eiji is a Developer Advocate for Chrome at Google. Eiji works closely with web application developers, helping them understand HTML5, open web technologies and WebStore. Before joining Google, he was leading SocialWeb effort on a portal site, developed the first Japanese OpenSocial container. He's also organizing developer community called SocialWeb Japan in his free time., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/eiji_kitamura.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/107085977904914121234/about

entry.title: Row: 11
entry.content: speakertitle: Chris Broadfoot, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Chris is a Developer Programs Engineer on the Geo Developer Relations team. He is currently focused on the Maps JavaScript API, helping developers build compelling applications. Prior to Google, he worked as a developer at Atlassian, CSC and Coca-Cola Amatil., speakerimageurl: https://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/chris_broadfoot.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/104108470253317688307/about

entry.title: Row: 12
entry.content: speakertitle: Marc Cohen, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Marc is a Developer Programs Engineer focused on helping developers get the most out of Google's advanced cloud computing technologies. He has over 25 years of experience designing and building reliable, distributed systems in the telecommunications industry. A Seattle native, Marc enjoys basketball, indie pop/rock music, and teaching Python Programming at the University of Washington., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/marc_cohen.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/100180575185522802900/about

entry.title: Row: 13
entry.content: speakertitle: Paul Saxman, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Paul is presently a Developer Programs Engineer on the Google TV team with a focus on Android app development. He has been programming for a couple of decades, and has worked on a variety of projects, including online games (BBS doors), non-interactive multimedia presentation (demos), embedded systems software, databased-backed dynamic web sites, interactive data visualizations, agent-based models, and mobile apps. Paul has a passion for analyzing and understanding complex data, and is a (bio)informaticist in heart and mind., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/paul_saxman.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/116049289435132333203/about

entry.title: Row: 14
entry.content: speakertitle: Wolff Dobson, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Wolff is a Developer Programs Engineer at Google working on social products. Before Google, he worked in the game industry for 12 years, including doing AI for Sega Sports and being one of the original developers of the Wii MotionPlus. He also, for some reason, has a PhD in artificial intelligence., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/wolff_dobson.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/103772069584080057731/about

entry.title: Row: 16
entry.content: speakertitle: Chris Schalk, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Chris is a Developer Advocate at Google who engages the cloud development communities with both Google App Engine and other Google cloud technologies. Chris joined Google in 2007 and has worked on various Google technologies including OpenSocial, Maps and AJAX Apis. Prior to Google, Chris was a Principal Product Manager at Oracle in the development tools group as well as co-author of "JavaServer Faces: The Complete Reference". Chris is a private pilot and also enjoys building and flying RC airplanes. When not flying, he also plays trumpet in various San Francisco Bay Area symphonies. Chris speaks Spanish, and a little French and German., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/chris_schalk.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/104599745903075924418/about

entry.title: Row: 17
entry.content: speakertitle: Alan Noble, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Alan Noble is a Engineering Director for Google Australia and New Zealand., speakerimageurl: https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-kiZm3ktGy8k/TZQFJJS41lI/AAAAAAAABzM/al8z9dIGOvQ/w100-h100-n-k/Alan_Noble_at_beach.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/105187180429104089107/about

entry.title: Row: 18
entry.content: speakertitle: Jeffrey Posnick, speakercompany: Google, speakerabstract: Jeff is a Senior Developer Programs Engineer based in New York City. He currently helps developers navigate the ins and outs of the YouTube APIs and understand the vagaries of video sitemaps. Before joining Google in 2007, Jeff spent time working in the financial and publishing industries., speakerimageurl: http://sites.google.com/site/developeradvocates/image/jeff_posnick.png, speakerurl: https://plus.google.com/117780118136555864520/about
